values.name: Unknown
values.description: Unknown - Azure Vm Security Suitability Detail

values.name: NotApplicable
values.description: NotApplicable - Azure Vm Security Suitability Detail

values.name: GuestOperatingSystemNotSupported
values.description: GuestOperatingSystemNotSupported Azure Vm Security Suitability Detail

values.name: BootTypeNotSupported
values.description: BootTypeNotSupported Azure Vm Security Suitability Detail

values.name: DiskSizeLarge
values.description: DiskSizeLarge Azure Vm Security Suitability Detail

values.name: AllDiskSizeExceeds4TB
values.description: Azure does not support VM with OS disk size greater than 4TB.

values.name: AnyDiskSizeExceeds4TB
values.description: Azure does not support VM with OS disk size greater than 4TB. If OS disk size is less than 4TB, proceed with migration.

values.name: AnyDiskSizeExceeds4TBConditional
values.description: Azure does not support VM with any disk size greater than 4TB. Please proceed only if you know the OS disk size is less than 4TB.

values.name: OSNotSupported
values.description: The VM is not ready to be migrated to Azure because the OS is not supported.

values.name: StandardReady
values.description: The VM is ready to be migrated to Azure with standard VM security type.

values.name: TVMReady
values.description: The VM is ready to be migrated to Azure with Trusted launch VM security type.

values.name: StandardNotReadyOSNotSupported
values.description: The VM is not ready to be migrated to Azure with standard VM security type because the OS is not supported.

values.name: TVMNotReadyOSNotSupported
values.description: The VM is not ready to be migrated to Azure with Trusted launch VM security type because the OS is not supported for Trusted launch VM. Get more information [here].

values.name: StandardNotReady2TBBiosBoot
values.description: The VM is not ready to be migrated to Azure with standard VM security type. Azure does not support OS disk size greater than 2TB for VMs with BIOS boot type.

values.name: AllDiskSizeExceeds2TB
values.description: The VM is not ready to be migrated to Azure with Trusted launch VM security type. Azure does not support OS disk size greater than 2TB for VMs with BIOS boot type.

values.name: DiskSize2TBConditionalReadyBiosBoot
values.description: The VM readiness is unknown. Azure does not support OS disk size greater than 2TB for VMs with BIOS boot type. Please proceed with migration only if OS disk size is less than 2TB.

values.name: TVMCannotMigrateOSNotSupported
values.description: The VM cannot be migrated to Trusted launch VM because the OS is not supported. Learn more [here].

values.name: StandardCannotMigrateOSNotSupported
values.description: The VM cannot be migrated to Azure because the OS is not supported.

values.name: StandardCanMigrate
values.description: The VM can be migrated to Azure with standard VM security type.

values.name: TVMCanMigrateConditional
values.description: The VM can be migrated to Trusted launch VM. Currently, Azure Migrate does not support migration to Trusted launch for VM with BIOS boot type. You can convert the VM post-migration to Trusted Launch VM. The steps are mentioned in this documentation.

values.name: OSNameCannotBeRead
values.description: Readiness is marked as unknown because the OS name cannot be read.

values.name: TVMNotSupportedForBiosBoot
values.description: Migration to Trusted Launch VM is not supported for BIOS boot type VMs at this time.
